originalQuery: Which are the top healthy vegetarian dog biscuit brands available online?
submittedQuery: Which are the top healthy vegetarian dog biscuit brands available online?
response:
Here are some top-rated healthy **vegetarian or plant-based dog biscuit brands** widely available online—ideal for pet owners seeking nutritious, animal-friendly snacks:

• **Wild Earth Superfood Dog Treats**  
  - Made with koji, a mushroom-derived protein, delivering all ten essential amino acids, omega fatty acids, and prebiotics for gut health([happycow.net](https://www.happycow.net/blog/plant-based-dog-treats-to-buy-for-your-furry-friends/?utm_source=openai)).  
  - Their treats use 90% fewer resources compared to meat-based options, appealing to sustainability-minded pet owners([happycow.net](https://www.happycow.net/blog/plant-based-dog-treats-to-buy-for-your-furry-friends/?utm_source=openai)).  
  - These are clean, plant-based treats with high nutritional value and are widely available online.

• **V-Dog Wiggle Biscuits & Breath Bones**  
  - These treats are plant-based, made with visible, wholesome ingredients like chia seed, flax, banana, coconut flakes, and are free from corn, soy, and wheat([happycow.net](https://www.happycow.net/blog/plant-based-dog-treats-to-buy-for-your-furry-friends/?utm_source=openai)).

• **Halo Garden of Vegan / Holistic Vegan Biscuits**  
  - Simple, crunchy biscuits baked in the U.S., made with ≤8 ingredients, offering 12% protein derived from peas and peanuts, and roughly 17 calories each([offthemrkt.com](https://www.offthemrkt.com/lifestyle/high-protein-vegan-dog-treats?utm_source=openai)).  
  - These are allergy-friendly (no wheat, corn, soy, animal proteins) and dental-friendly due to their firm texture([offthemrkt.com](https://www.offthemrkt.com/lifestyle/high-protein-vegan-dog-treats?utm_source=openai)).

• **Bright Planet Better Bac’n Bites**  
  - Soft, smoky bacon–flavored bites made from chickpea flour, sweet potato, and beet juice, each containing about 3–6 calories and around 10% protein([offthemrkt.com](https://www.offthemrkt.com/lifestyle/high-protein-vegan-dog-treats?utm_source=openai)).  
  - Hypoallergenic, environment-friendly treats where purchase supports planting trees([pawsdynasty.com](https://pawsdynasty.com/plant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).

• **Old Mother Hubbard Wellness Just Vegg’n Mini Biscuits**  
  - Oven-baked mini-size biscuits made with sweet potato, oats, apples, and carrots; natural, vegetarian, and great as low-calorie training rewards (~8 kcal each)([pawsdynasty.com](https://pawsdynasty.com/plant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).  
  - Affordable and widely available, though they contain grains which may not suit grain-sensitive dogs([pawsdynasty.com](https://pawsdynasty.com/plant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).

• **PETIPET Plant-Based Pumpkin Dog Treats**  
  - Soft, chewy treats made with organic pumpkin, carrot, apple, and blueberry—low-protein, gluten-free, and excellent for dogs with dental sensitivities or digestive issues([pawsdynasty.com](https://pawsdynasty.com/plant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).

• **Heads Up For Tails “Yummy in My Tummy” Pumpkin & Carrot Biscuits**  
  - Vegetables-based biscuits made with real pumpkin and carrot, free from artificial preservatives or animal products, making them healthy and suitable for sensitive pups([shopnow.hindustantimes.com](https://shopnow.hindustantimes.com/pet-supplies/pet-food-and-supplements/8-best-vegetarian-dog-food-to-buy-today-201679756349936.html?utm_source=openai)).

• **Riley’s Organics Small & Large Bone Baked Biscuits**  
  - Some options are cruelty-free and organic, such as peanut butter & molasses, pumpkin & coconut, apple, and sweet potato flavors; crafted with recognizable ingredients and supporting shelter donations([happycow.net](https://www.happycow.net/blog/plant-based-dog-treats-to-buy-for-your-furry-friends/?utm_source=openai)).

• **Grandma Lucy’s Organic Oven-Baked Dog Treats**  
  - Certified vegetarian and kosher; made with organic, all-natural ingredients, lacking GMOs, preservatives, and artificial colors([dogrs.com](https://dogrs.com/11-best-vegetarian-andplant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).

• **Fruitables Pumpkin Variety Pack**  
  - Oven-baked crunchy treats using fresh pumpkin blended with fruits such as apple, banana, blueberry, cranberry, sweet potato, and pecan; low in calories, high in fiber and antioxidants, U.S.-made([dogrs.com](https://dogrs.com/11-best-vegetarian-andplant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).

• **Superfood Science Plant-Based Treats**  
  - Made with sweet potato, chia, flaxseed, and coconut oil, these vegetarian, gluten-free treats support skin and coat health and are digestible and training-friendly([dogrs.com](https://dogrs.com/11-best-vegetarian-andplant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai)).

**Summary – Top Choices by Need**

• For **high protein & sustainability**: Wild Earth, V-Dog, Halo.  
• For **hypoallergenic or calorie-conscious treats**: Bright Planet Better Bac’n, Old Mother Hubbard Just Vegg’n, PETIPET.  
• For **organic/whole-food ingredients & ethical sourcing**: Riley’s Organics, Grandma Lucy’s, Fruitables, Superfood Science.  
• For **sensitive digestion and natural ingredients**: Heads Up For Tails Yummy in My Tummy.

Each of these brands offers healthy vegetarian or vegan formulations, free from artificial fillers, often with added nutritional benefits. Depending on your dog’s dietary needs—whether grain sensitivity, protein requirements, or weight management—these options offer a range of textures, flavors, and health profiles to suit.
